# Install

```
$ pip install lupe
```

## Features

- Parses arguments
- Outputs version when `--version` or `-v`
- Outputs description and supplied help text when `--help` or `-h`

## Usage

> There is not mango emoji yet supported. So instead, I used  a pear, but it kinda looks the same üòí
```
$ ./foo.py dinner --mango
```

```py
#!/usr/bin/python
# -*- coding: UTF-8 -*-

from lupe import *
from foo import *

cli = lupe(`
	Usage
	  $ foo <input>

	Options
	  --mango, -m  Include a mango

	Examples
	  $ foo dinner --mango
	  	dinner üçê
`, {
	flags: {
		mango: {
			type: 'boolean',
			alias: 'm'
		}
	}
});
/*
{
	input: ['dinner'],
	flags: {mango: true},
	...
}
*/

foo(cli.input[0], cli.flags);
```

